item.description:
I have canceled the Tuesday night snowshoe trip.  Everyone had backed out due to cold temps and wind.  Smart!

I have rescheduled for Thursday night at the same time - 6:00 PM.  The forecast is for much milder temps (40's!) and low winds, but partly cloudy.  It would be nice if everything could be perfect, but we live in New England and have to take what we get.  I will happily take a few clouds with milder temps and less wind!

People can stay to eat in the restaurant at the Country Club (Mulligan's Tavern) if they want.  I will probably not be able to stay.
item.how_to_find_us: In the parking lot with snowshoes!
item.why: The kayaks are still in hibernation.
item.name: Snowshoe under full moon at Westborough Country Club Golf Course
